The Harris fellowship from Harvard being awarded to him, he spent three years (1878–1881) in the study of physiological psychology in Berlin, Heidelberg, and Vienna.
He became musical editor of the New York Evening Post in 1881 and was on the editorial staff of the associated journal, The Nation.
He was connected with them for forty years.
